"EASY STARTS OFTEN HAVE THE MOST DIFFICULT PATHS"

So as the pic and the above quote states. We usually chooses the path that seems easy to our eye but it could have difficult path. This has become human nature ,we don't want to do hard work or strive a little as we think that choosing the first option we are saving time and energy but actually we are just going the wrong way and wrong way will never ever save anything neither time nor energy. We don't use our brains and think that the 2nd option may require some hard work initially but eventually it is the easiest path. Humans are used to shortcuts or things that are readily accessible. There can be one more reason, if one lazy person who indicates the first path people mostly follow that person only and if there is someone shows them the correct one they say that he or she is a fool as that person is telling them to actually do some productive work. We should learn to choose the correct path for us as well as for our future because only good and correct  path leads to the correct destinations.
